gnificantly weaker, $\\tau \\geq 60$~Gyr and $f<0.34$. Combining the CMB\nand WL data does not yield tighter constraints than the CMB alone, except for\nshort half-life times, for which the maximum allowed fraction becomes $f=0.03$.\nAll limits are provided at the 95% confidence level.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 25 Nov 2022 19:00:04 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 1 Mar 2023 13:44:31 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-04-19"}
